<p>
The first thought of creating an independent digital currency date back to 1992. In that year, Timothy May, a former Intel physicist, invited his friends to a house in Santa Cruz, to discuss the prospects of development of the Internet. By this time, Whitfield Diffie has created public key cryptography, and Philip Zimmermann - PGP-encrypted e-mail.
